verbs.description: materialize (third-person singular simple present materializes, present participle materializing, simple past and past participle materialized) (American spelling, Oxford British English)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To cause to take physical form, or to cause an object to appear.
(intransitive) To take physical form, to appear seemingly from nowhere.
examples: a spirit form, temporarily materialized, and undistinguishable from a human being in the flesh, has come forth in the light […]

entries.meaning: (transitive) To regard as matter; to consider or explain by the laws or principles which are appropriate to matter.
(transitive, databases) To perform materialization; to save the results of a database query as a temporary table or materialized view.
